[WIND WHISTLING]

22:59.504 --> 23:02.799
- How much further do we gotta go?
- I don't know.

23:03.633 --> 23:05.510
- Huh?
- Not much further.

23:05.677 --> 23:07.137
[BILLY CHUCKLES]

23:07.304 --> 23:09.681
That's what you said this morning.

23:10.891 --> 23:13.185
I sometimes say it all day.

23:13.351 --> 23:16.396
Really? You say it all day?

23:16.563 --> 23:19.274
We don't have much longer.
We'll be there soon.

23:20.067 --> 23:23.028
We gotta get to Mardi Gras, man.
We're going to Mardi Gras.

23:23.195 --> 23:25.530
Your little heart is set on that, huh?

23:26.114 --> 23:27.616
We got a week.

23:28.158 --> 23:30.577
That's a week away, man.

23:30.744 --> 23:33.538
BILLY:
It's a long way to Mardi Gras, baby.

23:34.790 --> 23:37.626
It won't take us a week
to get to New Orleans.

23:45.675 --> 23:47.052
Wow.

23:48.345 --> 23:50.639
Think I'm gonna crash.

23:51.056 --> 23:53.266
I think you have crashed, man.

23:56.812 --> 23:57.979
[BILLY GRUNTING]

24:04.569 --> 24:07.697
I keep seeing things
jumping all over the place.

24:08.532 --> 24:10.575
- Really?
- Yeah, look.

24:11.952 --> 24:13.703
- What is it?
- It's a moth.

24:13.870 --> 24:17.541
- A what?
- Moth. Bug.

24:24.214 --> 24:26.216
This is a weird place, man.

24:27.425 --> 24:29.761
That smoke's getting to me.

24:31.763 --> 24:34.349
But I notice you're not moving.

24:39.771 --> 24:41.815
BILLY:
Where are you from, man?

24:43.275 --> 24:45.443
Can I, uh--? Can I have a light?

24:45.610 --> 24:47.487
Where are you from, man?

24:50.448 --> 24:51.992
Hard to say.

24:52.159 --> 24:55.328
Hard to say? Where are you from, man?

24:55.495 --> 24:59.416
It's hard to say because it's
a very long word, you know?

25:00.750 --> 25:02.919
I just wanna know where you're from.

25:06.047 --> 25:07.340
The city.

25:07.966 --> 25:09.926
- From a city?
- Mm-hm.

25:11.261 --> 25:14.014
Doesn't make any difference what city.
They're all alike.

25:14.181 --> 25:15.891
That's why I'm out here now.

25:16.057 --> 25:19.811
- That's why you're out here? Why?
- Yeah.

25:20.270 --> 25:22.480
Because I'm a long way from the city...

25:22.647 --> 25:25.400
...and that's where I wanna be right now.

25:28.570 --> 25:30.864
They know you in this place?

25:32.991 --> 25:35.035
This place we're coming to?

25:35.452 --> 25:37.537
The place where we're at now?

25:39.122 --> 25:40.874
This place.

25:43.710 --> 25:45.712
[BILLY LAUGHING]

25:47.088 --> 25:49.007
You're right on top of them.

25:49.174 --> 25:51.635
- I'm right on top of them?
- Yeah.

25:52.135 --> 25:55.889
The people this place belongs
to are buried right under you.

25:58.308 --> 26:01.311
You could be a trifle polite.

26:01.478 --> 26:03.605
"A trifle polite"?

26:05.148 --> 26:07.567
A small thing to ask.

26:16.826 --> 26:19.329
You ever wanna be somebody else?

26:22.332 --> 26:25.085
I'd like to try Porky Pig.

26:30.715 --> 26:33.426
I never wanted to be anybody else.

26:53.863 --> 26:55.865
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

27:44.581 --> 27:46.583
[CHILDREN LAUGHING AND SHOUTING]

28:23.995 --> 28:25.872
BILLY:
Bam, bam! Ah!

28:26.039 --> 28:28.041
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

28:28.541 --> 28:30.543
[IMITATING GUNFIRE]

28:34.381 --> 28:36.549
You can't hit me.
I'm invisible! I'm invisible!

28:36.716 --> 28:38.259
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

28:44.099 --> 28:47.477
Hey, Sarah. How's it going?

28:55.527 --> 28:57.737
Rudolph, what are you eating?

28:59.739 --> 29:01.908
Thanks for the stuff you brought.

29:02.075 --> 29:03.451
STRANGER:
How's it going?

29:03.618 --> 29:07.789
SARAH: We can't take any more strangers.
Just too many people dropping in.

29:07.956 --> 29:11.584
Oh, I'm not talking about you and your friends,
you know that.

29:12.335 --> 29:16.339
Last week, Susan dropped in
with 12 people from Easter City.

29:16.506 --> 29:19.467
She wanted to take 10
pounds of rice with her.

29:19.634 --> 29:21.553
Naturally, we had to say no.

29:21.719 --> 29:25.765
So she gets uptight, breaks out some hash
and won't give us any.

29:25.932 --> 29:28.435
They went outside to start their bus...

29:28.601 --> 29:30.353
...and couldn't get it started.

29:30.520 --> 29:34.107
STRANGER: I bet you haven't had
anybody around like me to rap to.

29:34.274 --> 29:37.610
You know I love you and I want you to rap.

29:37.777 --> 29:40.405
- Oh, God, I want you to rap.
- Cut that out.

29:40.572 --> 29:43.199
I guess nobody else here is interested...

29:43.366 --> 29:45.952
...but I'd sure like to meet your friend.

29:46.119 --> 29:48.788
I bet you'd like to do more than that.

29:49.622 --> 29:51.166
I think he's beautiful.

29:51.332 --> 29:53.334
- He's beautiful.
- BILLY: Hey.

29:53.501 --> 29:55.712
What is that weird thing
up there on the hill?

29:55.879 --> 29:59.090
It looks like a stage.
You got a light opera company?

29:59.257 --> 30:01.050
That's the mime troupe stage.

30:01.217 --> 30:03.678
They've gone down to the
hot springs to bathe.

30:03.845 --> 30:05.680
Mime troupe?

30:07.765 --> 30:08.766
WOMAN:
Hey, Lisa?

30:08.975 --> 30:09.809
Oh.

30:09.976 --> 30:11.603
WOMAN:
What does this mean?

30:11.769 --> 30:15.106
"Starting brings misfortune.

30:15.523 --> 30:19.027
- Perseverance brings danger.
- Ta-da!

30:19.194 --> 30:23.615
Not every demand for change
in the existing order should be heeded.

30:23.781 --> 30:27.243
On the other hand,
repeated and well-founded complaints...

30:27.410 --> 30:29.746
...should not fail to a hearing."

30:29.913 --> 30:30.997
LISA:
Well, when one--

30:31.164 --> 30:33.708
MAN:
Hear ye, hear ye, hear ye!

30:34.083 --> 30:38.087
We've come to play for our dinner...

30:38.254 --> 30:41.883
...or should I say, stay for our dinner.

30:42.050 --> 30:44.219
Or even...

30:44.385 --> 30:46.554
...slay for our dinner.

30:46.721 --> 30:51.059
- Oh! Men at war. How ghastly, ghastly!
- Ah....

30:51.226 --> 30:53.728
We've come to drink your wine...

30:53.895 --> 30:58.066
...taste your food and take
pleasure in your women.

30:58.233 --> 31:00.860
The water in that river
is about 80 degrees.

31:01.027 --> 31:04.280
You put your hand in a foot
away, it's below freezing.

31:04.447 --> 31:07.408
SARAH:
Oh, come on. I've gotta get dinner on.

31:07.867 --> 31:09.202
Who said "out" to me?

31:09.369 --> 31:11.913
I picked-- Unhand me! I played communes--

31:12.080 --> 31:16.376
- Out! Out! Out! Out!
- Evil eye on this place.

31:16.543 --> 31:18.336
A double whammy for you all.

31:18.503 --> 31:20.755
[ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

31:20.922 --> 31:23.758
MAN:
Come, my dear. We won't play here.

31:23.925 --> 31:26.719
- BILLY: Wow, wow, wow.
- Wow.

31:26.886 --> 31:29.097
[BOTH GRUNTING AND MEOWING]

31:29.264 --> 31:30.682
SARAH:
Get out.

31:30.848 --> 31:32.934
- I like you.
- Ha-ha.

31:36.271 --> 31:38.273
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

31:41.359 --> 31:44.404
STRANGER:
These people got here late in the summer.

31:44.571 --> 31:47.574
Too late to plant.
But the weather was beautiful...

31:47.740 --> 31:50.994
...and it was easy living.
And then came that winter.

31:51.744 --> 31:54.747
There were 40 or 50 living
in a one-room place.

31:54.914 --> 31:59.669
Nothing to eat, out by the side of the road
looking for dead horses.

31:59.836 --> 32:01.713
Anything they could get ahold of.

32:01.879 --> 32:05.550
There's 18 or 20 left.
And they're city kids. Look at them.

32:11.431 --> 32:13.224
But they're getting this crop in.

32:13.391 --> 32:17.562
They'll stay here till it's harvested.
That's the whole thing.

32:24.861 --> 32:26.946
You get much rain here, man?

32:27.447 --> 32:30.241
I guess we'll have to dance for that.

32:43.630 --> 32:46.215
Look at this, man. A seashell. Dig.

32:46.382 --> 32:47.759
[BILLY MUMBLES]

32:51.012 --> 32:54.307
There's nothing but sand.
They ain't gonna make it.

32:55.308 --> 32:56.976
They're gonna make it.

32:57.644 --> 33:01.773
Dig, man. They're gonna make it.

33:11.157 --> 33:13.159
[CHILD CRYING]

34:37.076 --> 34:39.161
We have planted our seeds.

34:42.540 --> 34:43.958
We ask...

34:45.585 --> 34:47.712
...that our efforts be worthy...

34:48.963 --> 34:51.466
...to produce simple food...

34:52.592 --> 34:54.552
...for our simple taste.

34:57.722 --> 34:59.849
We ask that our efforts...

35:00.850 --> 35:02.518
...be rewarded.

35:07.148 --> 35:10.318
We thank you for the food
we eat from other hands...

35:15.865 --> 35:18.576
...that we may share it
with our fellow man...

35:20.912 --> 35:23.080
...and be even more generous...

35:24.081 --> 35:26.292
...when it is from our own.

35:32.131 --> 35:34.050
